BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:r9rocFnDoi0q6INP9bTJS
SUMMARY:Guest Stylist Pop-up Event
DTSTAMP:20260317T215823Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description      Nic of Ends of the Earth\, Micki Yeates of Hat
	ch Hair and Company\, and Kitt Spata are teaming up for a queer haircut da
	y Wednesday\, March 25th 11am - 5pm. Haircuts of all lengths are welcome\,
	 but each stylist specializes in slightly different services. If you don't
	 see a service that is appropriate for yourself with one stylist\, please 
	check the others'. This event is meant to be a fun time and designed to br
	ing community together and profits will go towards Kitt&'s travel costs as
	 well as a donation to Utopia Washington. Looking forward to seeing you th
	ere! Sliding scale options are available\, but spots are limited. Please u
	se the special booking link here to secure your appointment: Book Now\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/guest-stylist-pop-up-event/18
	234877/2026-03-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/guest-stylist-pop-up-even
	t/18234877/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Ends of the Earth Hair Studio\, 2430 32nd Ave W\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:JGMc2nHHPOxgvUAJ65TuP
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260317T215823Z
DTSTART:20260325T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-25T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - All Events
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-25T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-all
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - All Events
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
